Her Royal Highness, Olori Olufunmilayo Nejo-Oluyede, wife of traditional ruler of Ayede Ogbese in Akure North local government area, has commenced training of 50 teachers in pedagogy. The training which was done in collaboration with One Million Teachers training scheme was part of her empowerment programme for residents in the community. Olori Nejo-Oluyede said she decided to uplift the lives of Nigeria children by ensuring teachers who impact them with knowledge have the requisite and modern skills. She stated that it was to fix the dearth of skilled educationist in the country.   Kwara north beckons on Abdulrazaq to contest 2023…     INEC warns parties against conducting primaries outside…     Good governance key to sustainable development, says Oyetola   According to her, “You realised that education is key to the development of any society. There is dearth of well trained teachers globally. If you trained a teacher, you saved lives; you take people out of ignorance and out of a level of decadence. - Advertisement - The Alayede of Ogbese, Oba Ajibola Raphael Oluyede, said he supported the programme because it was a step towards making Nigerian graduates productive and employable. Oba Oluyede said it was important to impact the lives of the people in the community by training teachers. Deputy Governor of the State, Lucky Aiyedatiwa, who was represented by his Deputy Chief of Staff, Prince Omojuwa Olusegun, said the training was in line with the state government vision for the education sector.